column14: tweet

The economy of the future is one that we need to invest in, whether it's science, R&D, or a skilled workforce. But we also have to protect consumers and focus on consumer advocacy. I look forward to working with members of the @SenateCommerce committee on both sides of the aisle.
Great work being done by the Space Coast Basket Brigade, which delivers more than 2,000 #Thanksgiving meal baskets to families in need each year. #sayfie
Republicans control the House, Senate and the White House. A #TrumpShutdown would cost our economy millions of dollars and hurt American families right before the holidays.  https://t.co/HNymADx6Or

As a mom, it breaks my heart to see these images. These are families fleeing terror, violence & almost certain death.   It's disappointing to see our government treat refugee families this way. This is not the America I know & love. We are better than this. https://t.co/Jg0uCNVTLE

The #TrumpShutdown is holding hostage the emotional, health and fiscal well-being of 800,000 hardworking Americans and their families. This has gone on too long. It's time to reopen the government!  https://t.co/II6F76qEI5

As co-chair of the Senate CTE Caucus I have led efforts in the #Senate to strengthen #CTE & apprenticeship programs to help #Ohioans & Americans fill today’s in-demand #jobs. Apprenticeships are an important aspect of skilled labor & I’m proud to celebrate #NAW2018.

We have woken up too many times to the horrible news of a mass shooting in our country. My thoughts are with the victims and survivors of this massacre. Something must be done to address the gun violence epidemic plaguing our communities. #HonorWithAction  https://t.co/n4BppNiEDJ

This #ChristmasEve, I invite you to join me in praying for our men & women in uniform. May God bless our service members & their loved ones this holiday. I hope families in #TN03 are able to gather & remember the true reason for the season. I wish you & yours a #MerryChristmas.  https://t.co/zhPJRkaOKp

Honoring Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. — a true drum major for justice. The least I can do is be a cheerleader for justice, standing up for our federal employees and their families, and resisting Donald Trump. #MLK90 #MLKDay

The #shutdown could end tomorrow if Democrats were willing to negotiate w/ the President & support common sense border security that they’ve supported as recently as 2013. We don’t need band-aid solutions; we need to secure our border, aid hurricane victims, & reopen government.

Congrats to @SenPatRoberts & @SenStabenow on passing our strong 2018 #FarmBill conference report in the Senate. This bill is a real shot in the arm to rural America and I urge my colleagues in the House to join me in sending this bill to the president's desk.
Thank you @AndrewWarrenFL @ChadChronister for all you do to keep us safe everyday and ensure victims have all necessary care and support.

Diabetes is an #EverydayReality for those who live with it, including about 119,000 Mainers.  November is American Diabetes Month.  I applaud @AmDiabetesAssn, @JDRF, & others for raising awareness and making life better for all with #diabetes and their families.  https://t.co/82F4G1upp3

“While Trump continues to throw the government & some of its basic functions into chaos over money for a border wall, migrant children continue to die along that same border, at least in part because of the administration’s heartless immigration policies.”  https://t.co/eG23FPhE65

The #TrumpShutdown is endangering programs that assist N.J. working families and our most vulnerable. Trump needs to abandon his wasteful & unnecessary wall & reopen the government.   https://t.co/NZ7aO0ofDv

Jill & I were saddened to hear of Ed Pastor’s passing. We offer our heartfelt condolences to his wife, Verma, & the Pastor family. I was privileged to serve with him on Appropriations, where I saw how Ed fought tirelessly for his state & was beloved on both sides of the aisle.
As many celebrate Christmas Eve, my thoughts are with our military personnel far away from their loved ones. Thank you to all who serve and sacrifice.  https://t.co/fF40RHIXmx

Violence against Native American & Alaska Native women is a dire issue, w/ murder the 3rd leading cause of death. A new report on Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women and Girls by the Urban Indian Health Institute sheds an important light on the extent of the problem #MMIWG

The free & open internet is at the heart of what drives the American economy, opening doors to education & empowering small business. The @FCC must start listening to the voices of the American people & stop standing in the way of #NetNeutrality.  https://t.co/nd4jy2Po9E

Today, we all woke up to tragic news: another act of senseless gun violence. Our hearts are with the victims in Thousand Oaks, their families & the brave first responders who lost one of their own.  We can't grow numb to gun violence. It can't be the status quo. We need to act.

Hundreds of thousands of federal workers missed a paycheck on Friday because of the President’s senseless shutdown. This is jeopardizing the ability of families to pay their mortgages and put food on the table. The Trump shutdown needs to end now.
Today, we remember the 20 children and 6 staff members that were shot and killed at #SandyHook 6 years ago. Gun violence has taken far too many of our loved ones - young and old - far too soon.

For thousands living with and dying from 9/11-related illnesses, the tragedy of that horrific day continues. Stories such as this are why we have fought so hard for the #ZadrograAct, and why I will continue to fight to make the 9/11 VCF Program permanent.  https://t.co/VhUJgZWlrB

My heart is with the Thousand Oaks community this morning. Not one more life should be lost to gun violence. Congress must act now to keep our communities safe. #EnoughIsEnough  https://t.co/vqD6SwDqwW

President George H. W. Bush was a remarkable leader. He lived his life and led our nation with courage and conviction. He will be greatly missed. Erika and I send our deepest condolences to the Bush family during this difficult time.

The situation at the border is a self-inflicted wound. There was no strategy to handle families and children. Now we’ve had the death of a 7-year-old girl on the border. She is just one of the precious, innocent casualties due to mismanagement at the border. @cspanwj

I was proud to support this year's comprehensive farm bill that brings much needed security and support to hardworking Arkansas farm families, and I am pleased that the president signed it into law today. #AR02 #FarmBill

There are 7,471 federal workers and their families who are affected by the reckless and unnecessary #TrumpShutdown. These are our relatives, friends, and neighbors and @realdonaldtrump is harming communities across Illinois. He is causing long-term damage and enough is enough.  https://t.co/lwO8cc6gMB

.@realDonaldTrump is one turkey who should not be pardoned this #Thanksgiving. This week Trump helped the Saudis cover up the truth in #Khashoggi’s murder, attacked the Bin Laden raid leader, savaged an ind. judiciary, & avoided (again) going to a war zone to thank our troops.

The Weatherization Assistance Program (WAP) helps low-income families and seniors save money on their energy bills. Very pleased to see the Trump admin release critical resources today, following my bipartisan letter calling for an end to delays in WAP funding.  https://t.co/I1F57tfIxL

We should all be encouraging people to get affordable, high quality health coverage during open enrollment and letting them know how easy it is. Instead, President Trump’s Health Department is deleting information that helps families seeking coverage.  https://t.co/1KksNREMqc

Last year, the first bill I introduced when I got to #Congress was the “No Bonuses for Terrorists Act,” which would direct the Sec of State that the Palestinian Authority and PLO have ceased all financial rewards to terrorists or their families.

My heart is heavy as I mourn the loss of my dear friend Charles Brown - a brilliant and beautiful man, who was a pillar of our community. He passed into eternity on Thanksgiving Day.  May God bless his family, may his spirit live on, and may he rest in peace.

Today, @PhillyPolice Officer Paul Sulock was shot in the leg during an altercation. After he was wounded, Officer Sulock still pursued and apprehended a suspect. This is an incredible show of bravery. Wishing Officer Sulock a swift and full recovery.  https://t.co/rXeh25lHur

Arkansas's Medicaid work requirements have upended the lives of nearly 17,000 people who lost health coverage for no good reason. Arizona's families deserve better. CMS should deny Arizona's misguided request to implement work requirements.  https://t.co/nIwtWUfpDA

It's well past time for all American citizens detained by Iran to be home with their families & loved ones.  - Several of those families have written an open letter demanding action. Read it here:    https://t.co/XmhDwuS7Y3 @helpboblevinson

Our nation’s servicemembers upend their lives to serve our country & we need to make sure that when they come home, they can find meaningful work & provide for themselves & their families. I'm very happy that this important legislation was signed into law.  https://t.co/BSlWyA6wvo

I am saddened to hear this morning of the tragic loss of life in Afghanistan. This news is a grim reminder of our continued involvement in the region and of the constant dangers faced by our troops. Please join me in praying for these brave soldiers and their loved ones.

My district staff helped to bag and pass out groceries to hundreds of families at the recent Farm Share in Gadsden County. Food insecurity plagues so many in our community. This event…  https://t.co/mP6jEg8xK4

Today is the 77th anniversary of the attack on Pearl Harbor.  Let us remember the survivors and the more than 2,000 service members and civilians killed on “a date which will live in infamy.” We will never forget. #PearlHarborRememberance  https://t.co/ZWcnJLPIfM

Today I join the country in mourning the passing of one of America’s finest public servants, George HW Bush. His kindness, patriotism, and heart for public service will live on for years to come. #Remembering41  https://t.co/2Mv6BUd0QS
